  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health Care for 500 HIV+ Children in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides food, medicines, and a package of life saving health care services to 500 HIV+ children, and training in HIV to families. The package of services includes regular health check-ups, psycho social counseling, education in HIV, training and monitoring in adherence to medication and school support. After a few months, the children stabilize and/or improve in health so that they can attend school. Goal is to prevent new HIV infections and teach families self-reliance in health.</narrative>
  </description>
